        "changelog": "<h4>1.6.6<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>[NOTE] Adjusted sanitization for widget fields even further<\/li>\n<li>[NOTE] Tested up with WordPress 6.4.3<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.6.5<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>[NOTE] Upgraded analyst module to latest version<\/li>\n<li>[NOTE] Improved sanitization of widget fields <\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.6.4<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>[NOTE] Previous release didn&#8217;t contain all branches and code that should be included, adjusted<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.6.3<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>[FIX] Resolved reported issues with etw_hide_admin_notification_callback action<\/li>\n<li>[FIX] Adjusted plugin permissions in Multisite WP mode<\/li>\n<li>[NOTE] Tested with WordPress 6.4.2<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.6.2<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Updated &#8220;Try it out&#8221; module<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.6.1<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fixed incorrect calls to plugins_url<\/li>\n<li>Updated banner module<\/li>\n<li>Updated opt-in module<\/li>\n<li>Tested with WordPress 6.4<\/li>\n<li>Resolved issues with PHP 8.2<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.6.0<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Forced &#8220;Try it out&#8221; module to be disabled by default, user can still enable it manually.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.5.9<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Updated all plugin modules<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.5.8<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Limited access to editors+<\/li>\n<li>Tested the plugin with WP beta 6.3<\/li>\n<li>Updated carrousel module (added capability check)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.5.7<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Tested with WordPress 6.2<\/li>\n<li>Adjusted old database versions compatibility<\/li>\n<li>Updated carrousel module<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.5.6<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Adjusted PHP compatibility<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.5.5<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Added try it out module<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.5.4<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Tested up to WordPress 6.1-RC5<\/li>\n<li>Updated try it out URL in readme to properly setup demo site<\/li>\n<li>Adjusted carrousel module<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.5.3<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Added admin notice for new Widget editor<\/li>\n<li>Fixed Some minor fixes<\/li>\n<li>Tested up to WordPress 6.0-beta1<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.5.2<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Tested up to WordPress 5.7.1<\/li>\n<li>Added support for PHP 8<\/li>\n<li>Updated banner<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.5.1<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Tested with new version of WordPress<\/li>\n<li>Updated Opt-in<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.5<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fixed issue with not registered widget<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.4.9<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Rollback<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.4.8<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Tested with new version of WordPress<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.4.7<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Revival<\/li>\n<li>Added feedback system<\/li>\n<li>Updated readme<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.4.6<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Tested up to WordPress 4.8<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.4.5<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Adds option to hide empty widgets<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.4.4<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Updates tested to 4.0<\/li>\n<li>Updates license to GPLv3<\/li>\n<li>Minor code refactoring<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.4.3<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Adds Italian translation<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.4.2<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Removes widget caching<\/li>\n<li>Fixes issue with multiline PHP code<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.4<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Display text field in monospace font<\/li>\n<li>Code refactoring<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.3.4<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>This adds option to hide the title<\/li>\n<li>Tested up to 3.5.1<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.3.3<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fixes &#8220;Do not output before\/after_widget\/title&#8221; option<\/li>\n<li>Code cleanup<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.3.2<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Bug fixes<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.3<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fixed debug warnings<\/li>\n<li>Fixed code merge issue<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.2<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>This adds option to display bare text (no before\/after widget\/title elements are shown).<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.1<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Adds css class parameter that wraps widget.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.0<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>First release.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n",
